  <body>
    <p>
      <font face="SansSerif" size="4">&#36825;&#20010;&#22270;&#26159;Qt&#30340;&#24110;&#21161;&#25991;&#26723;&quot; Application Windows and Dialogs&quot;&#20013;&#20171;&#32461;&#30340;,&#26377;&#19968;&#20123;&#37325;&#35201;&#30340;&#25991;&#23383;&#25688;&#24405;&#22914;&#19979;: </font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-family: Arial, Geneva, Helvetica, sans-serif; margin-top: 8px; margin-left: 4px">
      <font color="rgb(103, 41, 103)"><a href="qwidget.html" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(103, 41, 103)">QWidget</a></font>&#160;provides several functions that deal with a widget's geometry. Some of these functions operate on the pure client area (i.e. the window excluding the window frame), others include the window frame. The differentiation is done in a way that covers the most common usage transparently.
    </p>
    <ul style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, Helvetica, sans-serif">
      <li>
        <b>Including the window frame:</b>&#160;<font color="rgb(103, 41, 103)"><a href="qwidget.html#x-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(103, 41, 103)">x()</a></font>,&#160;<font color="rgb(0, 70, 173)"><a href="qwidget.html#y-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 70, 173)">y()</a></font>,&#160;<font color="rgb(0, 70, 173)"><a href="qwidget.html#frameGeometry-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 70, 173)">frameGeometry()</a></font>,&#160;<font color="rgb(103, 41, 103)"><a href="qwidget.html#pos-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(103, 41, 103)">pos()</a></font>, and&#160;<font color="rgb(103, 41, 103)"><a href="qwidget.html#pos-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(103, 41, 103)">move()</a></font>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>Excluding the window frame:</b>&#160;<font color="rgb(0, 70, 173)"><a href="qwidget.html#geometry-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 70, 173)">geometry()</a></font>,&#160;<font color="rgb(0, 70, 173)"><a href="qwidget.html#width-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 70, 173)">width()</a></font>,&#160;<font color="rgb(0, 70, 173)"><a href="qwidget.html#height-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 70, 173)">height()</a></font>,&#160;<font color="rgb(0, 70, 173)"><a href="qwidget.html#rect-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 70, 173)">rect()</a></font>, and&#160;<font color="rgb(0, 70, 173)"><a href="qwidget.html#size-prop" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 70, 173)">size()</a></font>.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-family: Arial, Geneva, Helvetica, sans-serif; margin-top: 8px; margin-left: 4px">
      <font color="#ff0033"><b>Note that the distinction only matters for decorated top-level widgets. For all child widgets, the frame geometry is equal to the widget's client geometry. </b></font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
